"All severely malnourished children suffer from anaemia to some extent. After 15 days, when infection should in principle be controlled, all patients should therefore be given 1 mg of folic acid and 100 mg of ferrous sulphate daily for the duration of their stay in the TFC. \n# Routine treatment upon discharge\n\n# Immunization\nAll children should have been vaccinated against measles upon their admission, and be vaccinated again before their discharge. Moreover, all children should be immunized according to national guidelines. \n# Vitamin A\nAll patients are given a last dose prior to their discharge, according to recommendations made in Section 4.6.1 above."